The article is a transcript of a briefing with Shalanda Young, Director of the Office of Management and Budget, and Cecilia Rouse, Chair of the Council of Economic Advisers, discussing the 2023 budget. The budget focuses on deficit reduction, with plans to reduce the deficit by over $1.3 trillion. It includes investments in security, both domestic and abroad, and in various areas such as education, healthcare, and combating the opioid epidemic. The budget proposes tax reforms to ensure that corporations and the wealthiest Americans pay their fair share. The briefing also touches on the ongoing negotiations with Congress and the potential impact of the Russian invasion of Ukraine on energy and food prices.